PostgreSQL & Supabase Cursor Rules

1. Schema & Naming Conventions
- Case Sensitivity: Always use snake_case for tables, columns, and functions. 
- Never use CamelCase as it requires double-quoting in Postgres.
- Data types: use uuid for primary keys (default to gen_random_uuid()).
- Use timestamptz for all date/time fields. Use text instead of varchar(n) unless a specific length constraint is a business requirement.
- Relationships: Always define foreign keys with explicit ON DELETE actions (e.g., on delete cascade).

2. Security (RLS) & Performance
- Enable RLS: Every new table MUST have Row Level Security enabled immediately.
- Policy Granularity: Create separate policies for SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE.
- Indexing: Always index foreign keys to prevent full table scans on joins.
- Use gin indexes for jsonb or search-heavy columns.
- Functions: Use security definer sparingly and always set a safe search_path.

